This is the board state for a Tic Tac Toe game. 

The board state starts at the top-left corner with two open spaces in between. The first row represents the beginning of the game (e.g. player number X's turn), while the second row represents the start of another game (e.g. player number O's turn), with an emphasis on the front rows, i.e., "X" turns.

The game ends when a player reaches either the bottom right corner or the top left corner. If the player does not reach the end board, it is considered a draw. 

Overall, the Tic Tac Toe game has been around for decades and there have always been variations of this game.
